products.name: Resolve Spot+Stain Carpet & Rug Stain Remover Trigger Spray

extendedInfo.detail: Destroys tough messes 1st time. Penetrates deep to lift & remove stains like: Dirt; food grease; fruit juice; wine; tomato sauce & more. Cleans & refreshes. No. 1 carpet cleaning brand (Based on Nielsen data ending 52 weeks 05/06/20 unit sales of manual and machine formulas). Tomato sauce. Vegetable oil. Food grease. Mud. Tea. Salad dressing. Makeup. Pet stains. Dirt. Grass. Dirty motor oil. Red wine. Coffee. Cola. Fruit Juice. More. Questions? 1-800-228-4722 for more ingredient information visit www.rbnainfo.com.
extendedInfo.ingredients: Water, Hydrogen Peroxide, Sodium Lauryl Sulfate, Hexoxyethanol, Phenoxyisopropanol, Sodium Acrylates Copolymer, Tetrasodium Iminodisuccinate, Fragrance, Citric Acid, BHT.
extendedInfo.directions: How to use: Remove dirt. Spray & soak. Wait. Blot. Before Cleaning: Test a hidden section of carpet for colorfastness. Allow test area to dry completely and observe for any color change. Remove loose dirt and blot wet soils with a clean absorbent cloth. Directions for Use: 1. Spray area with Resolve. 2. Wait five minutes. 3. Blot or rub gently with a clean, damp, colorfast cloth or sponge. 4. Rinse sponge or cloth and repeat as necessary. For Best Result: Treat stains immediately. Set in stains can be more difficult to remove. Note that certain stains may cause permanent discoloration even after cleaning. Do not mix with bleach or in conjunction with other household products. Health. Hygiene. Home.
extendedInfo.warnings: Caution: Eye irritant. Read precautions on back.Caution: Eye irritant. May be harmful if swallowed. May cause skin irritation. Do not get directly in eyes, on skin or ingest.First Aid: If in eyes, immediately rinse eyes with plenty of water. Remove any contact lenses and continue rinsing eyes for at least 15 minutes. If irritation persists, get medical attention. If on skin, wash with plenty of soap and water. If irritation persists, get medical attention. If swallowed, rinse mouth and drink a glass of water. Call a physician or Poison Control Center.Keep out of reach of children. Contains hydrogen peroxide. Contains no phosphorus.
